abstract: Australia defeats Kuwait, 4-1, in opening match of Asian Cup soccer tournament in Melbourne; other soccer news noted.
lead_paragraph: Tim Cahill of the Red Bulls sparked a rally, and Australia beat Kuwait, 4-1, in the opening match of the Asian Cup in Melbourne.
snippet: Tim Cahill of the Red Bulls sparked a rally, and Australia beat Kuwait, 4-1, in the opening match of the Asian Cup in Melbourne.

headline.main: Tim Cahill Helps Australia Beat Kuwait in Asian Cup
